{"author":"Claude","data":{"alias":"catchable-specious-stilt","description":"## Why\nA folded state key is only useful if it is discoverable and durable. This story makes\n`claimed_session` a first-class, documented read field and proves it survives compaction.\n\n## What\n- Render `claimed_session` in `show` (next to `assignee`) and include it in the JSON\n  output and the MCP `show_ticket` `outputSchema`.\n- Confirm/guard compaction: `process_snapshot` restores it from `compiled_state`; add the\n  standard \"old snapshot lacks field -> default None\" guard so pre-feature snapshots don't\n  regress. Add a compaction round-trip regression test.\n- Optional: a `list --session=<id>` filter (\"what did session X claim?\").\n- Document the field + compaction/forward-compat behavior in `docs/event-schema.md`.\n\n## Scope\n- IN: read rendering, MCP outputSchema, docs, compaction default + round-trip test,\n  optional list filter.\n- OUT: capture shims (S4+), multi-harness provenance (S5).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `show <id>` displays `claimed_session` (and it appears in JSON output).\n- [ ] MCP `show_ticket` advertises `claimed_session` in its `outputSchema`.\n- [ ] Compaction round-trip preserves `claimed_session`; a pre-feature snapshot defaults it\n      to None without error (regression test).\n- [ ] `docs/event-schema.md` documents the field, precedence, and compat behavior.\n- [ ] (If included) `list --session=<id>` returns tickets claimed by that session.\n\n## Depends on\n- S2 (the state key exists).\n","id":"199b-f56f-5ba1-468b","parent_id":"38ec-5f12-fdf5-4340","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Expose claimed_session on the read surface + compaction-safety guarantee"},"env_id":"724d9d0c-bc4c-4cc4-b96b-1a19356102e2","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783481178879831827,"uuid":"d0e3dedf-49ed-4e83-8d60-701a61f69bfa"}